cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.CV 

This paper proposes a method for exploiting the underlying structures of the state-action value function for planning and deep reinforcement learning. The paper focuses on the low-rank structure, which is a common structure in big data matrices. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also includes experiments on control tasks and Atari games, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
